import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['US_Gross'] = data['US_Gross'] / 1000000
    data['Worldwide_Gross'] = data['Worldwide_Gross'] / 1000000
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.scatter(data['US_Gross'], data['Worldwide_Gross'], alpha=0.5)
    ax.set_xlabel('US Gross (in millions)')
    ax.set_ylabel('Worldwide Gross (in millions)')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of US_Gross and Worldwide_Gross?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Production_Budget'] = pd.to_numeric(data['Production_Budget'], errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna(subset=['Production_Budget'])
    plt.hist(data['Production_Budget'], bins=20, color='green')
    plt.axvline(data['Production_Budget'].median(), color='red', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['Production_Budget'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Production_Budget?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['Rotten_Tomatoes_Rating', 'IMDB_Rating']]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.boxplot(data.values, vert=False, showmeans=True, meanline=True, labels=data.columns)
    ax.set_xlabel('Rating')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of Rotten_Tomatoes_Rating and IMDB_Rating?')
    ax.axvline(data['Rotten_Tomatoes_Rating'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median Rotten Tomatoes Rating: {:.2f}'.format(data['Rotten_Tomatoes_Rating'].median()))
    ax.axvline(data['IMDB_Rating'].median(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median IMDB Rating: {:.2f}'.format(data['IMDB_Rating'].median()))
    ax.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
